"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769948","Department for International Trade","false","2017-10-20","<p>The Department for International Trade does not currently hold central data on the language skills of its workforce. Nevertheless, its workforce of over 3400 people operates successfully in over 108 markets. This requires a range of linguistic skills and abilities, especially in our overseas posts, which form part of the UK mission to that country.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-10-20T11:36:45.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769948/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769948/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769948/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-10-12","Department for International Trade: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many civil servants in his Department speak fluent (a) Mandarin, (b) Arabic, (c) Japanese and (d) Spanish.","false","Biography information for Mr Pat McFadden","Wolverhampton South East","Mr Pat McFadden","107628"
