"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768902","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-10-16","<p>We do not hold such data.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-10-16T12:05:57.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768902/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768902/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768902/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-11","Mass Media","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what information her Department holds on the number of news stories published in UK newspapers which have been identified by the (a) European Parliament and (b) European Commission as inaccurate in each year since 2005.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","107157"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768903","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-10-16","<p>No, the Department does not collect information on the gender balance among STEM subject staff at Tech City and Tech North.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-10-16T13:09:17.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768903/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768903/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768903/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-11","Tech City UK and Tech North: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 6 September 2017 to Question 9257, whether her Department collects information on the gender balance among STEM subject staff at Tech City and Tech North.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","107171"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768904","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-10-16","<p>We have held numerous discussions with Birmingham City Council regarding the opportunities to increase sport participation and physical activity as part of its bid to host the Commonwealth Games in 2022. Sporting legacy was a key criteria in the government's assessment process to select a UK candidate city and should Birmingham's bid be successful, legacy facilities will include a new swimming pool and an upgraded athletics stadium, which will include elite and community facilities.</p><p> </p><p>Should Birmingham be successful, we will continue to work with the city to maximise the opportunities to increase participation throughout the life cycle of the Games.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-10-16T16:06:14.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768904/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768904/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768904/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-11","Commonwealth Games: Birmingham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what discussions she has had with Birmingham Council on ensuring that that council receives a participation dividend in the event that Birmingham is successful in its bid to host the Commonwealth Games in 2022.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","107104"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768905","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-16","<p>The Red Arrows use the Hawk T1 aircraft which is due to remain in service until 2030. The UK currently has a pool of 75 T1 aircraft from which the Red Arrows are able to draw. Given the number of aircraft currently in service there is no pressing need to make a decision on Red Arrows replacement. Consideration will be given to replacing the Hawk T1 in due course but a decision is unlikely to be taken until after the end of the parliament.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-16T16:55:56.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768905/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768905/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768905/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-11","Red Arrows","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what his Department's plans are for the renewal of the jet aircraft used by the Red Arrows.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","107105"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768906","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-17","<p>The policy to remove the spare room subsidy applies to all working age Housing Benefit and Universal Credit claimants living in and under-occupying social housing without exception.</p><p> </p><p>A couple of easements apply. For example an extra bedroom is provided for those who require overnight care from a non-resident carer and for couples who are unable to share a bedroom due to disabilities.</p><p> </p><p>Since 2011, the Government has provided local authorities with around £900 million in Discretionary Housing Payment funding to support vulnerable Housing Benefit and Universal Credit claimants who are unable to mitigate the impact of welfare housing reforms.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-10-17T16:22:10.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768906/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768906/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768906/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-11","Housing Benefit: Veterans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what support his Department provides to ex-service personnel who face the under-occupancy charge.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kinnock","Aberavon","Stephen Kinnock","107118"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768907","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-16","<p>The Royal Navy employs a number of methods to recruit and retain personnel.</p><p>For recruitment the Royal Navy uses targeted advertising campaigns, web based and social media, radio and specific recruitment events. In addition, a range of mechanisms are used to attract and develop recruits including apprenticeship schemes and staged remunerative awards targeted at specialist areas.</p><p>In terms of retention of experienced personnel, a number of initiatives have been introduced, including targeted retention incentives and career extensions. Further developments under the Defence People Programme, such as flexible engagements, will help ensure that this process continues.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-10-16T16:39:19.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768907/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768907/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768907/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-11","Navy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps he is taking to increase the workforce of the Royal Navy.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","107111"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768908","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-16","<p>The Ministry of Defence remains committed to Defence and Security of the Falkland Islands and as such, protecting the right to self-determination. We undertake regular assessments of potential military threats to ensure that we retain an appropriate level of capability in the Falklands and a robust plan to rapidly reinforce, to address any such threats.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-10-16T16:54:53.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768908/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768908/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768908/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-11","Falkland Islands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether his Department has made an assessment of how the Falkland Islands could be recaptured in the event of invasion without the use of Royal Navy amphibious capabilities provided by HMS Albion, HMS Bulwark and HMS Ocean.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","107112"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768909","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-16","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) centrally manages the impact of variations in foreign exchange rates as part of the routine financial management of the defence programme. The foreign currency arrangements in place will limit the impact from the current foreign exchange position and any further considerations will be dealt with as part of the MOD's annual planning cycle.</p><p>This has not affected the projected procurement numbers of the aircraft listed.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-16T16:31:43.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768909/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768909/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768909/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-11","Military Aircraft: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the depreciation in the value of sterling has affected the projected procurement numbers of (a) F-35 fighter jets, (b) P-8 Poseidon maritime patrol aircraft and (c) Boeing Apache attack helicopters.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","107113"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768910","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-16","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave to Question 105167 on 10 October 2017 to the hon. Member for West Aberdeenshire and Kincardine (Andrew Bowie).</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-16T16:12:27.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768910/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768910/answer","20171010_105167_WQnA_on_Antiship_Missiles.docx","105167 - WQnA extract on Antiship missiles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768910/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-11","Antiship Missiles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans his Department has to replace the Royal Navy's Harpoon Anti-Ship missile after its retirement in 2018.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","107114"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768911","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-20","<p>The 20 civil servants within the Government Commercial Function were seconded to NATO Eurofighter and Tornado Management Agency and the Organisation for Joint Armament Cooperation.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-20T12:30:03.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768911/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768911/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768911/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-11","Ministry of Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 10 October 2017 to Question 10447, on Ministry of Defence: procurement, to which firms those 20 civil servants within the Government Commercial Function were seconded.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","107124"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768912","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-20","<p>The Queen Elizabeth Class Aircraft Carriers have been designed to operate as part of a Maritime Task Group in both the Carrier Strike and Littoral Manoeuvre roles, offering a significant basing option for the projection of air and amphibious power.</p><p>For operational security reasons, we do not comment on specific capabilities, as this would, or would be likely to, prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-20T12:31:41.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768912/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768912/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768912/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-11","HMS Prince of Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether HMS Prince of Wales has been designed to operate in littoral waters.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","107125"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768913","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-19","<p>The UK is not involved in counter-terror operations in Yemen. It is a long-standing policy of the Ministry of Defence not to comment on intelligence matters.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","107135","2017-10-19T14:31:05.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768913/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768913/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768913/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-11","Yemen: Counter-terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many suspected terrorists the Government has targeted in Yemen (a) on its own and (b) with the US since January 2017.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","107134"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768914","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-19","<p>The UK is not involved in counter-terror operations in Yemen. It is a long-standing policy of the Ministry of Defence not to comment on intelligence matters.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","107134","2017-10-19T14:31:05.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768914/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768914/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768914/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-11","Yemen: Counter-terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, on how many occasions the Government has authorised the use of (a) UK personnel, (b) UK assets, including RAF bases located in the UK and (c) UK intelligence in support of US counter-terror operations in Yemen.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","107135"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768915","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-19","<p>Any military support would only be provided to another State in accordance with our legal obligations and UK policy. UK military personnel providing such support would be appropriately briefed on those obligations and a military legal adviser would be available to advise.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-10-19T14:30:24.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768915/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768915/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768915/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-11","USA: Counter-terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what guidance is provided to UK personnel in support of US counter-terror actions outside of war zones.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","107136"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768916","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-19","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my hon. Friend the Minister of State for the Armed Forces (Mr Lancaster) on 21 January 2016 to Question 22264 to the hon. Member for Bridgend (Mrs Moon).</p><p>http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2016-01-13/22264/</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-10-19T14:29:06.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768916/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768916/answer","20160121_22264_WQnA_extract_on_Gulf_War_Syndrome.docx","22264 - WQnA extract on Gulf War Syndrome","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768916/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-11","Gulf War Syndrome","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps he has taken to invest in research on rehabilitation, health and social care models to improve the quality of life for Gulf War veterans who are experiencing ill health.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","107153"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768917","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-24","<p>BAE Systems remains a crucial industrial partner in supporting the Royal Navy in the Solent area. The Government is working with BAE Systems, Local Authorities, the Local Enterprise Partnership, and Talent Retention Solutions (TRS) to ensure that we retain vital engineering and manufacturing skills in the UK.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2017-10-24T12:10:19.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768917/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768917/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768917/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-11","BAE Systems: Redundancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps he is taking to ensure that skills in the defence manufacturing industry are retained across the Solent area following the announcement of proposed job losses at BAE Systems.","false","Biography information for Stephen Morgan","Portsmouth South","Stephen Morgan","107239"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768918","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-24","<p>BAE Systems officially confirmed their plans for company restructuring and potential job reductions on 6 October 2017. The proposals remain subject to Trades Union consultation and no final decisions have yet been taken. The Government will continue to work closely with the company to understand the impact of these potential reductions, to provide support to those who might be affected, and to maximise export opportunities for the Typhoon and Hawk training aircraft.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2017-10-24T12:09:44.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768918/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768918/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768918/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-11","BAE Systems: Redundancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, on what date the Government was first made aware of plans of the latest round of job losses at BAE Systems.","false","Biography information for Stephen Morgan","Portsmouth South","Stephen Morgan","107240"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768919","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-19","<p>In line with long standing commitments and ongoing defence engagement, the UK provides a small number of staff officers to United Nations Command in Korea and other headquarters across the Asia Pacific region.</p><p>The UK as a Sending State is committed to upholding peace and maintaining stability on the Korean peninsula. We will continue to work with our international partners to exert political and economic pressure on North Korea to change its direction and open the way to peaceful resolution.</p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon",,"2017-10-19T14:29:54.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768919/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768919/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768919/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-11","North Korea: Nuclear Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what support his Department is providing to the US in its response to the threat posed by North Korea.","false","Biography information for Leo Docherty","Aldershot","Leo Docherty","107207"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768920","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-19","<p>The Government has not authorised the use of lethal force by UK Armed Forces under the legal basis of self-defence of the UK in the time period specified.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-10-19T14:31:50.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768920/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768920/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768920/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-11","Law of War","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, on how many occasions since August 2015 the Government has authorised the use of lethal force in a non-military context under the legal basis of self-defence.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","107179"
