"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768007","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-16","<p>The Government’s plans to improve the energy efficiency of domestic properties are set out in the Clean Growth Strategy, published on Thursday 12 October.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-10-16T15:47:12.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768007/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768007/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768007/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-10","Housing: Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what plans he has to ensure the roll-out of improved energy efficiency in domestic properties.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","106935"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768008","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-17","<p>The European Union (Withdrawal) Bill will convert European Union law into UK law as it applies in the UK at the moment of exit. This will ensure that, wherever possible, the same rules and laws will apply the day after exit as they did before.</p><p>The Government is still making a detailed assessment of what corrections will be required to make that law function appropriately on exit day. The Department for Exiting the European Union are working closely with departments across Government to ensure we make the changes required to deliver a functioning statute book on exit in the most efficient manner possible.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-10-17T16:45:17.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768008/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768008/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768008/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-10","Department for Communities and Local Government: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what his Department's estimate is of the amount of EU legislation and regulation that can be incorporated into UK law without amendment.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","106996"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768009","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-16","<p>On 5 December 2016, Dame Louise Casey published her independent review of how to boost opportunity and integration in isolated and deprived communities. Since then my Department has been reviewing the available evidence on the main causes of poor integration. In the coming months we will bring forward plans for tackling these issues through a new integration strategy.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-10-16T16:11:19.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768009/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768009/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768009/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-10","Opportunity and Integration Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, when he plans to publish the Government response to the Casey Review.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","106973"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768010","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-16","<p>The Government’s consultation, 'Tackling unfair practices in the leasehold market', considered a number of issues within the leasehold sector including the sale of new built leasehold houses, and onerous ground rents. The consultation also sought views on what further areas of leasehold reform should be prioritised and why.</p><p>The public consultation, which closed on 19 September, received around 6,000 replies. We are carefully analysing the responses, and will issue the Government response shortly.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","106982 ; 106983","2017-10-16T10:39:19.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768010/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768010/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768010/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-10","Leasehold","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps the Government is taking to tackle high ground rent rates associated with new build properties sold on a leasehold only basis.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","106981"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768011","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-16","<p>The Government’s consultation, 'Tackling unfair practices in the leasehold market', considered a number of issues within the leasehold sector including the sale of new built leasehold houses, and onerous ground rents. The consultation also sought views on what further areas of leasehold reform should be prioritised and why.</p><p>The public consultation, which closed on 19 September, received around 6,000 replies. We are carefully analysing the responses, and will issue the Government response shortly.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","106981 ; 106983","2017-10-16T10:39:19.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768011/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768011/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768011/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-10","Leasehold","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what plans he has to tackle the practice of developers selling new build properties on a leasehold only basis; and what plans he has to prevent developers from applying such leasehold conditions to those homes intended as low-cost housing as a planning condition.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","106982"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768012","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-16","<p>The Government’s consultation, 'Tackling unfair practices in the leasehold market', considered a number of issues within the leasehold sector including the sale of new built leasehold houses, and onerous ground rents. The consultation also sought views on what further areas of leasehold reform should be prioritised and why.</p><p>The public consultation, which closed on 19 September, received around 6,000 replies. We are carefully analysing the responses, and will issue the Government response shortly.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","106981 ; 106982","2017-10-16T10:39:19.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768012/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768012/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768012/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-10","Leasehold","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what recent progress he has made on reforming the leasehold property system.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","106983"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768013","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-17","<p>We recognise the important contribution made by our emergency services to their communities. Their hard work and commitment to public service is celebrated the country over in local community events and also nationally.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2017-10-17T11:22:05.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768013/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768013/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768013/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-10","Emergency Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will make an assessment of the feasibility of establishing an event to mark the contribution that the emergency services make to communities and to thank them for the work they do during times of crisis.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kinnock","Aberavon","Stephen Kinnock","107056"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768014","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-18","<p>The Secretary of State has regular discussions with Cabinet colleagues on a range of local government matters, including finances.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-10-18T13:53:47.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768014/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768014/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768014/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-10","Local Government Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what discussions he has had with the Chancellor of the Exchequer on increasing the settlement for local government in the next budget.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kinnock","Aberavon","Stephen Kinnock","107057"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768015","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-10-16","<p>Government believes funding decisions should be made at a local level and local authorities are best placed to decide how to prioritise their spending. A locality’s cultural assets can be a major part of the local economy, attracting businesses and visitors, as well as providing a source of local pride and a sense of place.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2017-10-16T15:16:18.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768015/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768015/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768015/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-10","Culture: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment she has made of the level of spending by local authorities on projects related to culture and the arts in each of the last seven years.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","107065"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768016","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-10-16","<p>On 8 March 2017, Women in Sport published their Beyond 30% report which showed that 65% of the organisations funded by Sport England and/or UK Sport have more than 25% women on their boards. While this is a significant improvement on 2015, when the comparable figure was just 46%, clearly there is more to be done. This is why the Code for Sports Governance published last October requires funded organisations to adopt a target of, and take all appropriate actions to encourage, a minimum of 30% of each gender on its board. The governance code is mandatory for all sports bodies seeking public funding. National Governing Bodies who do not comply with the code will need to have agreed with the funding body an action plan which sets out how they will become compliant with that requirement by 31 October this year.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-10-16T15:50:27.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768016/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768016/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768016/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-10","Sports: Governing Bodies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what recent estimate she has made of the number of women on sports governing bodies.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","107063"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768017","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-10-16","<p>Problem gambling treatment, research and education is funded through a system of voluntary contributions by the gambling industry, and is administered through The Responsible Gambling Strategy Board and the charity GambleAware. GambleAware’s income for the last 5 years was (all financial years ending 31 March):</p><p> </p><p>2013 - £5,696,142</p><p>2014 - £6,277,934</p><p>2015 - £6,503,925</p><p>2016 - £7,632,371</p><p>2017 - £8,621,499</p><p> </p><p>Breakdown of expenditure can be found in GambleAware’s Annual Reports at https://about.gambleaware.org/about/annual-reports-minutes-newsletters/</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-10-16T16:04:15.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768017/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768017/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768017/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-10","Gambling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what level of funds her Department has spent on addressing problem gambling in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","107066"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768018","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-10-17","<p>The European Union (Withdrawal) Bill will convert European Union law into UK law as it applies in the UK at the moment of exit. This will ensure that, wherever possible, the same rules and laws will apply the day after exit as they did before.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is still making a detailed assessment of what corrections will be required to make that law function appropriately on exit day. The Department for Exiting the European Union are working closely with departments across Government to ensure we make the changes required to deliver a functioning statute book on exit in the most efficient manner possible.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-10-17T16:00:24.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768018/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768018/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768018/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-10","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what her Department's estimate is of the amount of EU legislation and regulation that can be incorporated into UK law without amendment.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","106997"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768019","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-10-18","<p>The European Electronic Communications Code (EECC) is still being negotiated within the EU. Trilogues have not yet even begun and therefore it is too early to say when the EECC will be adopted by the EU.</p><p>While the UK is still a ​Member ​State of the EU​, the UK will act in accordance with ​our rights and obligations associated with this.</p><p><em>​</em></p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-10-18T10:18:36.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768019/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768019/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768019/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-10","Telecommunications: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, whether the Government plans to implement the European Electronic Communications Code in the event that it becomes EU law (a) before any transitional period, (b) during any transition period and (c) after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Darren Jones","Bristol North West","Darren Jones","106876"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768020","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-10-16","<p>As with all funded sports, the Football Association is required to meet the obligations set out in Sport England and UK Sport’s funding agreements, which require appropriate safeguarding policies and procedures to be put in place and adherence to the Standards for Safeguarding and Protecting Children in Sport (the ‘Standards’) issued by the NSPCC’s Child Protection in Sport Unit (CPSU). The CPSU conducts an annual review of National Governing Bodies and reports back to ensure this funding condition is being met. During 2017, the CPSU has reported no concerns with the Football Association who continue to meet and maintain the advance Standards.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-10-16T15:48:50.963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768020/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768020/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768020/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-10","Football Association","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment her Department has made of the adequacy of the Football Association's safeguarding procedures.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","106871"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768021","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-10-16","<p>The cross-Government sport strategy ‘Sporting Future’ set out our intention to encourage as many people and groups to enjoy sport as participants, spectators and in the workforce, including the LGBT community. It also includes a number of other actions to ensure that all under-represented groups can take part in sport and wider physical activity through a focus on local delivery, and working with people through volunteering, coaching and the sporting workforce. Our aim is to increase diversity among sporting organisations and help the sport sector to be more inclusive and welcoming to all.</p><p> </p><p>Government continues to work with Sport England and National Governing Bodies of sport, alongside organisations including Pride Sports, Stonewall, and Kick it Out on a number of anti-homophobia initiatives aimed at encouraging inclusion. In March, Sport England commissioned Pride Sports to produce a second in depth report on barriers to LGBT participation. This research on volunteering, provision and attitudes and behaviours has been completed, and Sport England is currently considering what actions they will take based on the findings.</p><p> </p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-10-16T15:54:57.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768021/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768021/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768021/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-10","Sports: LGBT People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what steps her Department is taking to increase LGBT participation in sport.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","106868"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768022","Home Office","false","2017-10-16","<p>These data are not held by Government. The police take any allegation of abuse very seriously. A number of forces are investigating the allegations of abuse in football. Operation Hydrant is providing operational coordination of the allegations received by police forces across the country regarding non-recent abuse in football.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-10-16T14:34:29.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768022/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768022/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768022/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-10","Sexual Offences: Football","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many junior football coaches have been charged with sexual offences in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","106869"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768023","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-16","<p>The Government has initiated a review of national security capabilities in support of the continued implementation of the 2015 Strategic Defence and Security Review, to ensure the UK's investment in national security capabilities is as joined-up, effective and efficient as possible. Defence is contributing to this cross-Departmental effort, which is being overseen by the National Security Adviser. This work is on-going and no decisions have been made.</p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon",,"2017-10-16T14:14:19.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768023/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768023/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768023/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-10","Armed Forces: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether Joint Force 2025 will be affected by the review of the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","106862"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768024","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-17","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) is procuring nine P-8A Poseidon maritime patrol aircraft under a Foreign Military Sale (FMS) arrangement with the US Government. Delivery of the first aircraft is expected in 2019. The estimated total cost is $3.2 billion. This figure includes the cost of the aircraft, and also encompasses initial support, training, sonobuoy and weapons provisioning, together with training devices.</p><p>The MOD is also purchasing 50 Apache AH-64E helicopters, also under a FMS arrangement with the US Government at an estimated cost of $2.3 billion. This figure includes an initial two-year support package, spares, training simulators and other supporting equipment for the helicopters.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-17T13:58:36.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768024/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768024/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768024/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-10","Military Aircraft: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the commitments set out in the 2015 Strategic Defence and Security Review, what the forecast value is of his Department's future orders for (a) P8 Maritime Patrol Aircraft and (b) Apache AH-64E helicopters.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","106940"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768025","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-16","<p>The Government has initiated work on a review of national security capabilities in support of the continued implementation of the 2015 Strategic Defence and Security Review, to ensure the UK's investment in national security capabilities is as joined-up, effective and efficient as possible in the face of intensifying threats. Defence is contributing to this cross-Departmental effort, which is being overseen by the National Security Adviser.</p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon",,"2017-10-16T14:12:57.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768025/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768025/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768025/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-10","Strategic Defence and Security Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when his Department plans to publish the results of its review of the 2015 Strategic Defence and Security Review being undertaken by its Director for Strategic Planning.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","106954"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768026","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-17","<p>The Secretary of State fully understands the importance of Bombardier to Northern Ireland and has been closely engaged on this matter, meeting with both the Secretaries of State for Northern Ireland and Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy in support the Government's approach.</p><p>Alongside this and as part of the wider Government efforts, we have made it clear to Boeing that this is not the behaviour we would expect from a long-term strategic partner and we have also raised our concerns about potential impact on Northern Ireland with the US Administration.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-17T13:57:31.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768026/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768026/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768026/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-10","Bombardier: Belfast","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland on the potential job losses at Bombardier in Belfast; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","106941"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768027","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-16","<p>We continuously review the capabilities we require. The National Security Capability Review is focussed on the continued implementation of the 2015 Strategic Defence and Security Review, to ensure the United Kingdom’s investment in national security capabilities is as joined-up, effective and efficient as possible. No decisions have been made and any discussion of specific platforms or capabilities is speculation.</p><p>On current plans the out of service dates for these vessels is provided below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Ship</p></td><td><p>Out of Service Date</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS OCEAN</p></td><td><p>2018</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS ALBION</p></td><td><p>2033</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS BULWARK</p></td><td><p>2034</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","106958 ; 106959","2017-10-16T16:13:07.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768027/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768027/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768027/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-10","Warships: Decommissioning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the current planned operational retirement date is for (a) HMS Albion, (b) HMS Bulwark and (c) HMS Ocean.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","106955"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768028","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-16","<p>We continuously review the capabilities we require. The National Security Capability Review is focussed on the continued implementation of the 2015 Strategic Defence and Security Review, to ensure the United Kingdom’s investment in national security capabilities is as joined-up, effective and efficient as possible. No decisions have been made and any discussion of specific platforms or capabilities is speculation.</p><p>On current plans the out of service dates for these vessels is provided below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Ship</p></td><td><p>Out of Service Date</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS OCEAN</p></td><td><p>2018</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS ALBION</p></td><td><p>2033</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS BULWARK</p></td><td><p>2034</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","106955 ; 106959","2017-10-16T16:13:07.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768028/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768028/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768028/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-10","Warships: Decommissioning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will make an assessment of the potential loss of (a) HMS Albion and (b) HMS Bulwark on the ability of the Royal Marines to deploy overseas.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","106958"
