"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768030","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-17","<p>Information on how much the Ministry of Defence has paid to Boeing in each of the last five years is provided below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Value* (million)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>£348</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>£493</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>£488</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>£499</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>£524</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2"><p><em>*figures rounded to the nearest million</em></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>This information is also published in the Trade Industry &amp; Contracts Statistical Bulletin, which can be found at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/defence-trade-and-industry-index" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/defence-trade-and-industry-index</a></p><p> </p><p>It is worth noting, however, these figures do not include the acquisition of Boeing capabilities made through Foreign Military Sales agreements with the US Government, such as the new AH-64E Apache Attack Helicopters and P-8 Poseidon Maritime Patrol Aircraft.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-17T13:58:27.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768030/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768030/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768030/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-10","Boeing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department has paid to Boeing in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","106939"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768031","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-18","<p>The European Union (Withdrawal) Bill will convert European Union law into UK law as it applies in the UK at the moment of exit. This will ensure that, wherever possible, the same rules and laws will apply the day after exit as they did before.</p><p>The Government is still making a detailed assessment of what corrections will be required to make that law function appropriately on exit day. The Department for Exiting the European Union are working closely with Departments across Government to ensure we make the changes required to deliver a functioning statute book on exit in the most efficient manner possible.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-10-18T15:53:11.91Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768031/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768031/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768031/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-10","Ministry of Defence: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what his Department's estimate is of the amount of EU legislation and regulation that can be incorporated into UK law without amendment.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","106998"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768032","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-17","<p>The cost of the work on the last refit of HMS Albion was around £90 million.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-17T14:24:08.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768032/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768032/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768032/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-10","HMS Albion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the recent refit cost of HMS Albion was.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","106949"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768033","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-16","<p>As at 1 April 2017, we had 38 M3 amphibious bridging vehicles. We do not routinely comment on specific levels of readiness and specific locations for individual capabilities as to do so would compromise operational security, or would, or would be likely to, prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p><p> </p><p>38 UK M3 amphibious bridging vehicles have been based in Germany in each of the last 10 years.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","106985 ; 106986 ; 106987","2017-10-16T16:45:20.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768033/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768033/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/768033/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-10","NATO: Military Exercises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many M3 amphibious bridging vehicles were deployed during NATO exercises in each of the last 10 years; what the name of the (a) exercise and (b) unit was engaged in each of those exercises; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","106984"
